.Dd April 21, 2026
.Dt QLAUDE 1
.Os "qlaude 0.1.0"
.Sh NAME
.Nm qlaude
.Nd Claude session utilities
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar account
.Ar command Op Ar args No ...
.Pp
.Nm
.Op Ar account
.Cm conv Op Ar conv-args
.br
.Nm
.Op Ar account
.Bro Cm skills | Cm agents | Cm plugins | Cm touch Brc
.br
.Nm
.Ar account
.Cm launch Op Ar claude-args
.br
.Nm
.Cm config Op Ar subcommand Op Ar args
.br
.Nm
.Bro Cm help | Cm h Brc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a utility for managing and inspecting Claude Code sessions across one or
more accounts.
It provides a conversation viewer with cost-weighted token usage bar charts,
resource listing
.Pq skills, agents, plugins ,
keepalive touches, account configuration management, and a launcher that
sets
.Ev CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR
to the correct base directory.
.Pp
Most commands accept an optional
.Ar account
prefix to scope the operation to a single Claude Code installation.
When omitted, commands operate across
.Em all
configured accounts.
The only hardcoded account is
.Sq default
pointing to
.Pa ~/.claude .
Additional accounts are registered with
.Cm qlaude config add-dir .
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Cm conv Op Ar conv-args
Display token usage statistics for Claude Code conversations.
Produces a one-line entry per conversation with a cost-weighted bar chart
showing input, output, cache-create, and cache-read token segments.
With no arguments, prints detailed usage information.
See
.Sx CONV COMMAND
below for the full range syntax.
.It Cm skills
List subdirectories under each account's
.Pa skills/
directory.
.It Cm agents
List subdirectories under each account's
.Pa agents/
directory.
.It Cm plugins
List plugin names parsed from each account's
.Pa plugins/installed_plugins.json .
.It Cm touch
Send a minimal keepalive message to Claude for each account.
When an explicit account is given, touches only that account.
.It Cm launch Op Ar claude-args
Launch
.Xr claude 1
with
.Ev CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR
set to the base directory of the specified account.
An explicit account name is required.
Remaining arguments are passed through to
.Xr claude 1 .
.It Cm config Op Ar subcommand Op Ar args
Manage account directories and display settings.
With no subcommand, opens an interactive configuration TUI.
See
.Sx CONFIG COMMAND
below.
.It Cm help
Print detailed help and exit.
.El
.Sh CONV COMMAND
.Nm
.Op Ar account
.Cm conv
.Ar range-or-count Op Fl -detailed
.Pp
The
.Cm conv
command reads
.Pa *.jsonl
conversation files from each account's
.Pa projects/
tree.
It parses token-usage fields from assistant messages and renders a bar chart.
The bar length reflects the total token count; bar segment widths reflect the
relative cost contribution of each token type
.Pq output 50\(mu, input 10\(mu, cache-create 12.5\(mu, cache-read 1\(mu .
.Pp
Bar legend:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
\(br\(br\(br\(br\(br\(br   input
\(sq\(sq\(sq\(sq   output
\(br\(br\(br   cache-create
\(sc\(sc\(sc   cache-read
\(bu\(bu\(bu   empty
.Ed
.Pp
The
.Fl -detailed
flag switches from one-line entries to a multi-line view with a per-type
token breakdown.
.Ss Range forms
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Cm conv Ar N
Show the
.Ar N
most recent conversations.
.It Cm conv Ar A Ns - Ns Ar B
Show conversations ranked
.Ar A
through
.Ar B
by recency.
.It Cm conv just Ar N
Show only the
.Ar N Ns th
most recent conversation.
.It Cm conv Fl Ar n Ar unit Op Cm through Fl Ar m Ar unit Op Ar N
Show conversations within a calendar period.
.Ar unit
is one of
.Bro Cm hour(s) | Cm day(s) | Cm week(s) | Cm month(s) | Cm year(s) Brc .
.Fl 0
refers to the current period,
.Fl 1
to the previous one, and so on.
The optional
.Cm through
clause extends the range to a second (more recent) period.
The optional trailing
.Ar N
caps the result count.
.It Cm conv live
Enter live-watcher mode: display the most recently modified conversation and
refresh automatically on each change.
Press
.Sy q
to exit.
Uses
.Xr fswatch 1
when available, polling otherwise.
.El
.Ss Aliases
The following word aliases expand anywhere in a range expression:
.Bl -tag -width "yesterday" -compact
.It Cm today
.Fl 0 Cm day
.It Cm yesterday
.Fl 1 Cm day
.It Cm this
.Fl 0
.It Cm last
.Fl 1
.El
.Ss Display configuration
Conv display settings are managed via
.Cm qlaude config .
The following keys are relevant:
.Bl -tag -width "max_tokens" -compact
.It Cm max_tokens
Bar ceiling in fixed-norm mode
.Pq default 20000000 .
.It Cm scale
.Cm log No or Cm linear Pq default linear .
.It Cm tokens
.Cm actual No or Cm scaled Pq default actual — scaled applies cost weights to the displayed count .
.It Cm norm
.Cm fixed No or Cm dynamic Pq default fixed — dynamic sets ceiling to the longest conversation in view .
.It Cm w_input , Cm w_output , Cm w_cc , Cm w_cr
Cost weights ×10
.Pq defaults: 100, 500, 125, 10 .
.It Cm live_mode
.Cm override No or Cm scroll — whether live refreshes overwrite the previous line or append .
.El
.Sh CONFIG COMMAND
.Nm
.Cm config Op Ar subcommand Op Ar args
.Pp
Without a subcommand, opens an interactive menu-driven TUI for editing
accounts and display settings.
.Ss Subcommands
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Cm list
Print all current settings, including account directories and display values.
.It Cm path
Print the path to the config file.
.It Cm get Ar key
Print the current value of
.Ar key .
For
.Cm accounts No or Cm dirs ,
prints all account name/path pairs.
.It Cm set Ar key Ar value
Set
.Ar key
to
.Ar value
and save the config file.
.It Cm add-dir Ar name Ar basedir
Register a new primary account named
.Ar name
with base directory
.Ar basedir .
.Ar basedir
should be a Claude Code config directory
.Pq contains projects/, skills/, etc .
.It Cm add-alias Ar alias Ar name
Create a secondary alias for an existing account.
The alias is not added to the
.Dq all accounts
iteration list.
.It Cm remove-dir Ar name
Remove a primary account and all secondary aliases that point to the same
directory.
.It Cm reset Op Fl -yes
Delete the config file and restore script defaults.
Prompts for confirmation unless
.Fl -yes
is given.
.El
.Ss Config keys
.Bl -tag -width "max_tokens"
.It Cm max_tokens
Positive integer.
Bar length ceiling when
.Cm norm
is
.Cm fixed .
.It Cm scale
.Cm log No | Cm linear .
Bar length scaling mode.
Log compresses large conversations so smaller ones are still visible.
.It Cm tokens
.Cm actual No | Cm scaled .
Whether the displayed count is the raw token total or the cost-weighted total.
.It Cm norm
.Cm fixed No | Cm dynamic .
Fixed uses
.Cm max_tokens
as the bar ceiling for all conversations in a view.
Dynamic scales to the largest conversation in the current result set.
.It Cm w_input , Cm w_output , Cm w_cc , Cm w_cr
Positive integer, representing the cost weight ×10.
Larger values make that token type take proportionally more bar space.
.It Cm live_mode
.Cm override No | Cm scroll .
In
.Cm override
mode
.Pq default ,
each live refresh overwrites the previous line.
In
.Cm scroll
mode, each refresh appends a new line.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Ss Browsing conversations
Show the 10 most recent conversations across all accounts:
.Dl $ qlaude conv 10
.Pp
Show conversations 16 through 20:
.Dl $ qlaude conv 16-20
.Pp
Show only the 3rd most recent:
.Dl $ qlaude conv just 3
.Pp
Show this week's conversations:
.Dl $ qlaude conv -0 week
.Pp
Show last week through this week, capped at 20:
.Dl $ qlaude conv last week through this week 20
.Pp
Show a detailed multi-line breakdown of the last 5:
.Dl $ qlaude conv 5 --detailed
.Pp
Watch the most recent conversation live:
.Dl $ qlaude conv live
.Ss Scoping to an account
Show skills for a specific account named
.Sq sbq :
.Dl $ qlaude sbq skills
.Pp
Launch Claude for that account:
.Dl $ qlaude sbq launch --resume
.Pp
Touch all accounts:
.Dl $ qlaude touch
.Ss Managing accounts
Add a second Claude Code account:
.Dl $ qlaude config add-dir sbq ~/.claude-sbq
.Pp
Add a short alias for an existing account:
.Dl $ qlaude config add-alias s sbq
.Pp
Show all configured accounts and display settings:
.Dl $ qlaude config list
.Pp
Remove an account (and all its aliases):
.Dl $ qlaude config remove-dir sbq
.Ss Tuning the bar display
Use log scaling to make small conversations more visible:
.Dl $ qlaude config set scale log
.Pp
Switch to dynamic normalization so the bar ceiling matches the longest result:
.Dl $ qlaude config set norm dynamic
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ev CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR
Set by
.Cm launch
to the account's base directory before invoking
.Xr claude 1 .
.It Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the
.Nm
config file.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config .
The config file is stored at
.Pa ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/qlaude/config.zsh .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Pa ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/qlaude/config.zsh
Account directory map and display settings.
Sourced as zsh on startup; auto-generated by
.Cm qlaude config .
When this file is present it fully replaces the script defaults.
.It Pa <basedir>/projects/
Claude Code conversation files
.Pq *.jsonl ,
one subdirectory per project.
Scanned by
.Cm conv .
.It Pa <basedir>/skills/ , <basedir>/agents/ , <basedir>/plugins/
Resource directories listed by the corresponding
.Nm
commands.
.El
